Moreno may not have much interest in getting in touch with his
inner golfer _ ``The same four of us have played together for eight
years, and we're just out there to have a good time'' _ but he knew
something about ``Chicken Soup for the Golfer's Soul'' when it was
pointed out to him on Golfsmith's shelf last week.
</P>
<P>
   ``My wife has them all,'' Moreno said of the ``Chicken Soup''
books. ``If she comes over here and sees it, she'll probably buy it
for me for Fathers Day.''
</P>
<P>
   Just don't expect Mike Lazzo to buy it.
</P>
<P>
   ``If the golf course really was like life,'' he sighed, ``nobody
would play.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
