<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    George W. Bush highlights
 &HT;    (For Sunday, June 20. Package includes BUSH-PROFILE-COX-TAKE1,
BUSH-PROFILE-COX-TAKE2, BUSH-PROFILE-COX-TAKE3, BUSH-TIMELINE-COX
and photos. A shorter version of the profile is moving as
BUSH-PROFILE-SHORT-COX. This version is also available for sale as
a full-page layout at www.nytsyn.com/pageexpress.)
 &HT;    
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Jan. 6, 1945: George Herbert Walker Bush marries Barbara Pierce.
</P>
<P>
   July 6, 1946: George Walker Bush is born in New Haven, Conn.
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 24, 1963: Upon returning to prep school at Phillips
Academy in Andover, Mass., George W. Bush gives this report on his
summer: ``I started off the summer with a bang at Tennis Week in
Rye, N.Y. then proceeded to work on a cattle ranch in Williams,
Arizona, after which I visited Moondog Kidde and participated in
the unexciting sport of surfing.''
</P>
<P>
   Fall 1967: Campus cops at Princeton University yell at Bush and
other Yalies for bringing down goalpost after football game.
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 5, 1973: Bush requests discharge from Texas Air National
Guard to attend Harvard Business School.
</P>
<P>
   1977: Using leftover money from education trust fund, Bush forms
the oil firm Arbusto Exploration Inc. Meets and marries Laura
Welch.
</P>
<P>
   November 1988: George H.W. Bush elected 41st president.
</P>
<P>
   January 1991: Arlington voters approve $135 million bond issue
to build The Ballpark for Bush's Texas Rangers baseball team.
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 8, 1994: George W. Bush elected governor of Texas with 53.3
percent of vote.
</P>
<P>
   April 15, 1999: Bush pays $3.8 million in federal income taxes
for 1998 on estimated taxable income of $18.4 million _ $14.9
million of it from Bush's stake in the sale of the Rangers.
</P>
<P>
   June 12, 1999: Bush makes first major speech of still-undeclared
presidential campaign.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
