<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Some people I know are
worried about Y2K supplies or cellulite on their upper thighs or
getting their daughter into a good middle school. But I say these
people are self-absorbed and misguided. I say these people have
their priorities all mixed up. What we all should be worrying about
is the millions of Americans who use cell phones to make calls from
the most ridiculous of places, including bathroom stalls. (Minor,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ Nothing worse than being broke in
the big city. And I'm as good as broke if I can't break this $100
bill. So I go and stand in line at a bank where I don't have an
account, and expect the worst. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED
TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ ``How low can you get?'' That's
what Dennis Faughn of Enon thought when he learned that two
teen-agers had robbed his 9-year-old son's lemonade stand. If ever
there were a today's-youth-is-going-to-hell-in-a-handbasket crime,
this would be it. (McCarty, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ will not move today.
</P>
<P>
   JEFFERSON-COLUMN _ will not move today.
