<P>
   RECLINERS _ Five fathers ``test drive'' the latest styles of
recliners _ and we're here to tell you, these are not your
grandfather's Barcaloungers. (MJohnson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-THERAPY _ DAYTON, Ohio _ If you've got a personal
problem, a computer and a credit card, Susan Wright is ready to
help. Just head to her web site _ www.advicelink.com _ fill out a
12-question survey about your troubles and offer up your credit
card number. For $25, Wright, a licensed independent Cleveland
social worker, will e-mail her counsel back to you. Witness the
birth of a service known as e-therapy or webcounseling, the
delivery of mental health services over the Internet. Its methods,
many believe, will lead to permanent changes in the field. The
question is whether that will be for the better. (Keilman, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GARAGESALE-CLASH _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The yard sale begins
at 8, but three women dressed in cottony bright island colors show
up before 7 in the bleakest of Toyotas. They move up the driveway,
fan out like a recon patrol, look over the merchandise, which is
still being lugged out of the garage by the bleary-eyed homeowner.
One of the early shoppers spies a small cast-iron garden pot
bearing a $10 price. She lifts the pot, turns to the hostess of the
yard sale. ``Fifty-cent.'' ``Fifty-cents?'' says the homeowner, her
tone saturated with incredulity. ``It's marked ten dollars.''
``Fifty-cent.'' The homeowner shrugs. Her posture and facial
expression say ``no dice.'' She turns to another early customer.
The lady with the pot says nothing, puts the pot down, moves on to
a pile of children's clothes. She picks up a little dress, marked
$2. ``Fifty-cent,'' but nobody's listening. Why is no one
listening? A Haitian made the bid, and frankly, there is an uneasy
truce between newly arrived immigrant shoppers and longtime area
residents who hold garage sales. It's simple, really. One culture's
buying customs clash with the selling customs of another. (Reid,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
