planning his Chicago debut, a two-acre space at the heart of the
city's jewel-like lakefront that he has been asked to turn into a
music pavilion complete with proscenium arch, pedestrian bridge and
Central Park-like Great Lawn. By Pam Belluck.
</P>
<P>
   LOLITA-PREQUEL (Undated) _ A deal is struck with Vladimir
Nabokov's heir on a ``Lolita'' prequel. By Peter Applebome.
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-BURARGUE (Rio de Janeiro) _ Arts Abroad: Chico Burargue's
