UNDATED: room temperature. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tuna
</P>
<P>
   8 tuna steaks (6 ounces each)
</P>
<P>
   Mango glaze
</P>
<P>
   Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper
</P>
<P>
   Preheat a gas or charcoal grill to medium high. Brush the tuna
steaks on both sides with 1 1/2 cups of the mango glaze and season
with salt and pepper. Grill 2 to 3 minutes on each side for
medium-rare doneness. Arrange the steaks on a platter and
immediately brush with the remaining cup of mango glaze. Serve with
black bean salad.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving including salad, dressing,
glaze and tuna: 620 calories, 25 grams fat, 49 grams carbohydrates,
50 grams protein, 77 milligrams cholesterol, 75 milligrams sodium,
36 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _''Boy Meets Grill''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CHICKEN BREASTS IN LIP-SMACKIN' BARBECUE SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   4 cups Lip-Smackin' Barbecue Sauce, recipe follows
</P>
<P>
   6 skinless bone-in chicken breast halves, rinsed under cold
water and patted dry
</P>
<P>
   Place the barbecue sauce in a large saucepan and bring to a
simmer over medium heat. Add the chicken breasts. When the sauce
returns to a simmer, reduce the heat to low and simmer for 40
minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through. Remove the chicken
from the sauce and serve immediately, passing the sauce at the
table.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LIP-SMACKIN' BARBECUE SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons olive oil
</P>
<P>
   2 cups chopped sweet onions (such as Vidalia or Texas Sweet)
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon minced garlic
</P>
<P>
   1 cup brewed strong coffee
</P>
<P>
   1 cup Worcestershire sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 cup tomato ketchup
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup cider vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup packed dark brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup chopped canned mild green chiles
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chili powder
</P>
<P>
   Place a 4-quart saucepan over medium-high heat and add the oil.
When it is hot, add the onions and garlic and saute until softened,
4 to 5 minutes. Reduce the heat to medium and whisk in the
remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to low and
simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Let cool.
</P>
<P>
   In a blender or food processor, puree the sauce in batches until
smooth. Store any remaining sauce, covered, in the refrigerator for
up to 2 weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving using 4 tablespoons of barbecue
sauce per serving: 258 calories, 5 grams fat, 16 grams
carbohydrates, 37 grams protein, 96 milligrams cholesterol, 446
milligrams sodium, 17 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _''A Guy's Guide to Great Eating''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ASPARAGUS WITH PARMESAN CHEESE AND PROSCIUTTO
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   Lemon-caper vinaigrette
</P>
<P>
   Yields 3/4 cup
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup fresh lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup olive oil
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons capers
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley
</P>
<P>
   Freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   Whisk together lemon juice and olive oil in small bowl. Add
capers and parsley and season with black pepper. May be
refrigerated for 1 day; serve at room temperature. Makes about 3/4
cup.
</P>
<P>
   Asparagus
</P>
<P>
   24 asparagus spears, trimmed and peeled
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil
</P>
<P>
   Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper
</P>
<P>
   8 thin slices prosciutto
</P>
<P>
   Lemon-caper vinaigrette
</P>
<P>
   Thinly shaved slices of Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   Preheat a gas or charcoal grill to high.
</P>
<P>
   Toss asparagus with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and
grill 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Wrap a piece of prosciutto
around 3 asparagus spears and place on a platter; repeat with
remaining asparagus and prosciutto. Drizzle with vinaigrette and
top with Parmesan cheese.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving with vinaigrette: 200 calories,
19 grams fat, 4 grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 7 milligrams
cholesterol, 249 milligrams sodium, 85 percent of calories from
fat.
</P>
<P>
   _''Boy Meets Grill''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LIVIN'-LARGE PECAN PIE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6-8
</P>
<P>
   2 large egg yolks
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted
</P>
<P>
   6 large egg whites
</P>
<P>
   1 1/3 cups dark corn syrup
</P>
<P>
   1 1/3 cups granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 1/4 teaspoons vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup pecan halves, sliced lengthwise into slivers
</P>
<P>
   9-inch unbaked store-bought reduced-fat deep-dish pie crust
</P>
<P>
   Place the oven rack in the lower-middle position and preheat the
oven to 350 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the egg yolks and melted
butter until combined. Add the egg whites and whisk until frothy.
Whisk in the corn syrup, sugar and vanilla until the sugar
dissolves. Stir in the pecans.
</P>
<P>
   Pour the mixture into the pie crust, place the pie pan on a
jelly-roll pan, and bake for 60 to 65 minutes, or until a knife
inserted halfway between the center and the edge comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack and serve.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 479 calories, 14 grams fat, 86
grams carbohydrates, 7 grams protein, 85 milligrams cholesterol,
270 milligrams sodium, 26 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _''A Guy's Guide to Great Eating''
</P>
