burgeoning medical research community. But other states are seeking
this research, too. By Ronald Rosenberg. 680 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-RAIL-CSX (Boston) -- Former Conrail train lines in
Massachusetts are now part of the CSX transportation network,
offering shippers one-line service to as far away as Miami and the
Deep South. By Peter Howe. 1600 words.
</P>
<P>
   ONJOBS-COLUMN (Undated) -- The superwomen of an earlier
generation worked outside and returned eight hours later to run the
home. These days, their daughters are remaking the rules. By Diane
E. Lewis. 1000 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Internet stocks have been falling
as investors seem to be turning to more traditional companies
again. But so far the downturn has affected the market in general.
By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
