 &HT;    Spotlight on. . . .
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Michael Caine (`Little Voice')
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Alfie'' (1966): Showing us what's it all about in
swinging1960s London.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Sleuth'' (1972): Matching wits with Laurence Olivier in this
two-person thriller.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Man Who Would Be King'' (1975):
</P>
<P>
   Adventuring with Sean Connery in John Huston's epic adventure.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``California Suite'' (1978): Bickering as a closeted gay man
married to Maggie Smith in Neil Simon's comedy.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Dressed to Kill'' (1980): Looking like Linda Tripp in Brian
De Palma's gory homage to
</P>
<P>
   Hitchcock.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Hand'' (1981): Battling his own possessed digits in this
Oliver Stone flick.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Mona Lisa'' (1986): Playing a pimp opposite Bob Hoskins in
Neil Jordan's dreamy-gritty mystery.
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
