<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SOFTWARE HEADS FOR TOP ROLE IN U.S. ECONOMY
 &HT;    Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories
 &HT;    By Andrew J. Glass
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON The digital code that powers the nation's computers
provided a record $141 billion upward kick to the domestic economy,
according to a study released Wednesday by a key software trade
group.
