<P>
   BKN-GEORGE-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Go back exactly 11
years. It is mid-June, so steamy that birdbaths bubble. In a Palm
Beach County motel room sits a pro basketball player, his eyes on
the NBA playoffs, his dream captured inside a 19-inch TV screen.
Truly the United States Basketball League, a summer option for
players who just won't quit, is death by disassociation. No one
back in 1988 would have associated Avery Johnson with the NBA
Finals. Yet when the San Antonio Spurs take the court Wednesday for
Game 1 of the NBA Finals, it will be Avery Johnson pounding the
ball up the court as a trusted associate of Tim Duncan and David
Robinson. It is mid-June in 1999 and everything has changed.
(George, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
