<P>
   &UR; SETTLEMENT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Pristina, Yugoslavia) _ Scorning minefields and
efforts to organize their return, refugees flood across the borders
back into Kosovo. By Charles A. Radin. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-KLA (Djakovica, Kosovo) _ Putting their weapons away, at
least for now, the KLA quickly emerges as the
political-administrative power in the ravaged town of Djakovica. By
Susan Milligan. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-EUROPE (Geneva) _ President Clinton calls for a
worldwide ban on the worst forms of child labor, saying the time
has come to ``wipe from the earth'' child slavery and prostitution,
and drug trafficking. By Ann Scales. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   SAFRICA-MBEKI (Pretoria) _ South Africa inaugurates Thabo Mbeki.
By Kurt Shillingere. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE-VIOLENCE (Washington) _ House debates ways to curb youth
violence _ from gun-control measures to regulating the
entertainment industry to allowing prayer in schools. By Louise D.
Palmer. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GORE-DECLARE (Carthage, Tenn.) _ Al Gore announces his run for
the presidency, and not-so-subtly tries to put some distance
between himself and Bill Clinton. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CHIMPS-RELATIONSHIPS (Undated) _ Scientists say chimpanzees can
identify relationships between other chimps they don't know, just
by seeing pictures of their faces. By David L. Chandler. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PRICES (Undated) _ Government reports that consumer prices were
unchanged in May, putting an end to April's inflation scare and
confirming that the nation's remarkable era of low inflation and
strong economic growth is continuing. By Kimberly Blanton. 800
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-TWINS-REDSOX (Boston) _ By Gordon Edes.
</P>
