<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEES (Vermitca, Yugoslavia) _ More than 12,000
cheering, stunned Albanians begin their journey home, in the first
big wave of a reverse exodus of refugees who were driven from
Kosovo in a Serbian campaign of terror. Their departure created the
kind of chaos for refugee agencies that aid workers had feared. By
mid-afternoon, the line of honking, over-loaded cars, trucks and
tractors up the crumbling road out of Albania toward this Kosovo
border village was 5 miles long. By Elisabeth Bumiller. (We plan to
move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) 1,300 words.
</P>
<P>
   The story runs under a 4-column photo of returning refugees.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RDP (Patres) _ The Kosovo Liberation Army's leaders have
pledged to cooperate with NATO's peacekeepers, but so far they have
not shown much inclination to break up their insurgency _ just as
it has become the dominant political and military force among
Kosovo's Albanians.In the most serious of a series of
confrontations between NATO troops and the KLA, American marines
with helicopter gunships overhead confiscate the weapons of more
than 100 of the insurgents and detain six of their leaders. By
Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) 1,300
words.
