   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   ECON-REPORT (Undated) _ After haunting investors for weeks, the
threat of inflation suddenly retreats _ at least for now. The
consumer price index, which jumped 0.7 percent in April, did not
rise at all in May, the Labor Department reports. And the closely
watched ``core'' inflation rate _ which excludes volatile food and
energy prices _ edged up a mere 0.1 percent versus a 0.4 percent
increase in April. By Sylvia Nasar. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m.
ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
