   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   SUMMER-SCHOOL (New York) _ As New York City prepares for the
nation's largest mandatory summer school program _ starting with
70,000 students next month and growing to as many as 362,000 next
year _ the experience in Boston and Los Angeles shows that the
logistical hurdles will be formidable. What it does not show
conclusively is whether mandatory summer school works. By Randal C.
Archibold. 2,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CHIMP-CULTURE (Undated) _ The world's most eminent experts
on chimppanzees, pooling decades of research, have come to a
startling conclusion: The primates mostly closely related to humans
in various parts of Africa behave in widely varying ways and teach
these ways to their offspring. In short, they exhibit what up to
now had been thought of as a strictly human traint _ culture. By
Natalie Angier.
</P>
