<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Minorities making gains on corporate boards
 &HT;    By Shannon Shelton
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Ethnic minorities continue to increase their presence
on the boards of America's top corporations, according to a
Korn/Ferry International study.
</P>
<P>
   Sixty percent of the nation's 903 largest corporations have at
least one ethnic minority director, up from 55 percent in 1998.
African-Americans are on 39 percent of all boards, Latinos on 12
percent and Asians on 9 percent, Korn/Ferry said.
</P>
<P>
   The percentage of boards with women increased slightly, to 73
percent this year from 72 percent in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
