<SLUG> BC-ECOMMERCE17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Total System in e-commerce coalition
 &HT;    By Ernest Holsendolph
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A new alliance of companies, including Total System of
Columbus, announced a coalition Wednesday to introduce products and
services to bolster electronic commerce among businesses.
</P>
<P>
   The group, called the Global Commerce Alliance, plans products
for many tasks, ranging from buying and selling, billing and
bill-paying, and target marketing of goods.
</P>
<P>
   Among the members of the alliance are GE Capital, Global
Commerce Systems Inc., Sun Microsystems and SunConnect Framework,
as well as Total System Services Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Even as the alliance was being introduced, Total System unveiled
its first product, called TSYS Total Commerce, a system for
managing a supply chain for business-to-business electronic trade.
</P>
<P>
   Total Commerce is the first in a series of products that the
alliance expects to ``co-brand.''
</P>
<P>
   Don Charron, TSYS group vice president and director of corporate
development, said:
</P>
<P>
   ``TSYS Total Commerce enables information to reach the right
part of the organization at the right time, providing access any
time, anywhere to real-time financial transaction data.''
</P>
<P>
   The product is based on contributions not only by Total System
but also by Global Commerce Systems. By enabling the users of the
product to work in real time, the new systems make sure the
businesses are on the same page as they do transactions.
</P>
<P>
   One of the objectives of the alliance is to speed transactions
and introduce streamlining impossible with paper-based
technologies. By using the special capabilities of the individual
players in the alliance, the companies said they hope to introduce
new e-commerce products and services rapidly over the next three
years.
</P>
<P>
   ``We believe that by leveraging our large-scale credit card
transaction processing and customer self-service over the Internet
with ... (alliance members) puts us in a better position to serve
our clients around the world,'' said Philip W. Tomlinson, president
of TSYS.
</P>
<P>
   Total System is one of the world's leading processors of data
transactions involving domestic and overseas users of credit, debit
and other cards.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
