<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JUNE 17
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-SCHAWLOW-NYT (moved on Thursday, Apr. 29)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Arthur L. Schawlow, sent by the New York Times
News Service on Thursday, April 29, misstated the achievement for
which he was cited. A reader pointed out in mid-May that it was
contributions to the development of laser spectroscopy, not the
development of lasers. (This correction was delayed for checking of
several questions raised by the letter.)
</P>
<P>
   BC-GERTRUDE-STEIN-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 8,
about ``Gertrude and Alice: A Likeness to Loving,'' a new play
about the relationship between Gertrude Stein and Alice B. Toklas,
referred incompletely to the editorship of two volumes of Stein's
writings published last year by the Library of America. Harriet
Scott Chessman was a co-editor, with Catharine Stimpson.
</P>
<P>
   BC-FISH-BOOK-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 15,
about ``Fish,'' a cookbook by Sophie Grigson and William Black,
misstated its price at Kitchen Arts and Letters in Manhattan. It is
$45, not $55.
</P>
