A cemetery in Brooklyn does not publicize its tombs' Tiffany
windows, like this one from the ``River of Life'' series, behind an
iron grille. Louis Comfort Tiffany's special effects,
pre-Spielberg, were built at the height of turn-of-the-century
religious fervor, when church-building was a national pastime and
extravagant tombs were embellished with art. (Suzanne DeChillo/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) CHOLULA, Mexico -- June 16, 1999 -- MEXICO-QUAKE, 6-16
-- In St. Francis church in Cholula, a shrine to Mary, workers
salvage valuables Wednesday. Those inside were unhurt by the
earthquake, which struck central Mexico at 3:42 p.m. Tuesday with a
magnitude of 6.7 on the standard seismic scale. By the latest
official count, 16 people perished under falling roofs and walls,
and dozens were injured. (Wesley Bocxe/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- June 16, 1999 -- TV-NICKELODEON-SCANNELL,
6-16 -- Herb Scannell, the chief executive of Nickelodeon, at the
children's TV network offices in New York. Scannell, 42, says many
of his best ideas come to him at home, an apartment in lower
Manhattan where he lives with his wife, Sarah, and their 4-year-old
daughter, Caroline. And though a company car could be at his
disposal, Scannell takes the subway to work. ``Only three stops on
the express train,'' he says. (Jeffery A. Salter/New York Times
Photo) LITE
</P>
