Setize Hase tries to console her on Wednesday after returning to
the village. Ms. Mucolli said her parents, four sisters, two
sister-in-laws, six nieces and nephews were killed by Serbs. Ethnic
Albanians who fled Kosovo returned to the region to find mass
graves strewn with personal effects lying near where the victims
were killed. (Alan Chin/New York Times Photo)
