KOSOVO-REFUGEES-2, 6-16 -- Vehicles carrying ethnic Albanians
returning to Kosovo clog a road near Kukes near the Albanian border
on Wednesday. In the first wave of a massive reverse exodus of
refugees who were expelled from their homes in a Serbian campaign
of terror and ethnic cleansing, close to 15,000 Kosovar Albanians
began the journey home, creating the very crisis that refugee
agencies had feared. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
