more complicated for homeowners who live in historic houses and who
want to maintain the period accuracy of their homes. For them, it
is important to know what colors were available when and how they
were used by decorators. A general knowledge of color history can
also be helpful because it provides a source of inspiration for
contemporary design schemes. (Edward R. Lipinski/New York Times
Illustration) LITE
